author: Sam Warner
title: X Factor: BEKLN replace Rumour Has It to complete Group category - The X Factor Reality TV
text: Cheryl Fernandez-Versini faced a tough decision this evening on The X Factor with one final swap to complete her groups category in the Six Chair Challenge.The judge promised boy band BEKLN a seat after their performance of 'See You Again' by Wiz Khalifa and Charlie Puth, Fernandez-Versini eventually deciding to drop girl group Rumour Has It. © ITV / Thames/Syco/Fremantle MediaBEKLN at the X Factor Six Chair Challenge Cowell told her beforehand to "protect the singers", with Fernandez-Versini saying that she wanted "reliability" in her category.She then decided to swap Rumour Has It with BEKLN, Cowell exclaiming "I mean seriously?"However, Rita Ora showed approval for Fernandez-Versini's decision. © ITV / Thames/Syco/Fremantle MediaRumour Has It at The X Factor Six Chair Challenge Earlier, the groups judge gave Silver Tone a seat too.The final line up in the groups category is Menn On Point, Alien, BEKLN, 4th Power, Silver Tone and The First Kings.The X Factor is showing on ITV now.
